  title: Can I store the result of the condition in a bool and test that?
  text: "Yup! You can place the condition directly in the if\n##REF##code,if (a <
    3) {\n    // Do something\n}##REF##\nOr store the condition result in a bool
    variable and use that directly in the if\n##REF##code,\nbool condition = a <
    3;\nif (condition) {\n    // Do something\n}\n##REF##\nBy the way remember you
    can also revert the condition value with a ! NOT\n##REF##code,\nbool condition
    = a < 3;\nif (!condition) {\n    // Do something\n}\n##REF##\n"
